definition: temple (on the sides of human head)

sentences.english: A running gag in the show has vegetation grow from his temple whenever he thinks too hard.
sentences.chinese: 每次他努力思考的时候太阳穴都会长出植物来。

sentences.english: The blood throbbed in her temples.
sentences.chinese: 她太阳穴里血管卜卜跳。

sentences.english: Human Josh lifts the link rig and rubs his temples.
sentences.chinese: 人形的Jake掀开顶盖，揉了揉自己的太阳穴。

sentences.english: Just over each temple there were little blue veins .
sentences.chinese: 就在两鬓太阳穴上面显露著青色的细小静脉。

sentences.english: My head throbs behind my eyes and in the temple.
sentences.chinese: 我的眼睛后方和太阳穴有搏动的感觉。

sentences.english: The gunshot wound to Lien Chan's son's right temple is not believed to be life-threatening, the report said.
sentences.chinese: 报道说，连战儿子右太阳穴的枪伤并不威胁生命。

sentences.english: I had moistened his temples, and had given him some water to drink.
sentences.chinese: 我用水渍湿了他的太阳穴，让他喝了点水。

sentences.english: Lastly, there are the temporal lobes, near the temples, which are involved with hearing and memory.
sentences.chinese: 最后面是颞叶，它在太阳穴附近，关系到听觉和记忆。

sentences.english: Good for temporal migraine and nose congestion and menstrual cramp.
sentences.chinese: 太阳穴偏头痛及鼻塞，经痛均有效。

sentences.english: I could feel sweat pouring down my temples.
sentences.chinese: 我感到汗从太阳穴一直往下滴。

sentences.english: And he gave him another hit on the temple with his clenched fist.
sentences.chinese: 然后他又打了郑屠一拳，打在他的太阳穴上。

sentences.english: My eyes clouded over and the blood pulsated in my temples.
sentences.chinese: 我眼前一片云雾，热血在我太阳穴里突突地跳动。

sentences.english: Jack pulls her out of the car and places his gun at her temple.
sentences.chinese: 杰克把她扯出了她的车外，用枪指着她的太阳穴。

sentences.english: One shot has been fired into his right temple and his service revolver was still in his hand.
sentences.chinese: 他向自己的太阳穴开枪，手上仍然拿著自己的配枪。

sentences.english: Jaw muscles and clenched, and temple or neck veins throb.
sentences.chinese: 下巴肌肉紧绷着，太阳穴或脖子上青筋突出。

sentences.english: His temples throbbed with the rush of blood.
sentences.chinese: 隐士血流奔涌，太阳穴随之悸动。

definition: the wing of the nose/ala nasi
